Cell.Text: "Long live the Emperor! Long live the Empire!"

Node.Caption: MQ102ALegionOath3: May those above judge me, and those below take me, if I fail in my duty.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Welcome to the Imperial Legion, soldier. | Just remember, we take care of our own. Once you're in the Legion, you're in it for life. | Now, if I'm not mistaken. Legate Rikke has a special assignment for you.

Node.Caption: MQ102ALegionOath4: Long live the Emperor! Long live the Empire!

Cell.Text: S|In joining the Legion, you'll be taking a sacred oath, binding you to the service of the Emperor and thus to every citizen of the Empire.
Changed your mind? Decided you want to soldier for the Emperor after all?

Node.Caption: MQ102JoinLegionBranchTopic: I'd like to join the Imperial Legion.

Cell.Text: G|I see... Well, the Legion will still be here when you change your mind. Rikke believes in you. I'm coming around about you myself. | Consider this. What greater glory than to serve the Emperor and his citizens here in Skyrim, in these days of her greatest need?

Node.Caption: MQ102JoinLegionNo: Actually, I'm not sure. I need to think about it.

Cell.Text: Well, then. Repeat after me. | "Upon my honor I do swear undying loyalty to the Emperor..."

Node.Caption: MQ102JoinLegionYes: I'm sure. I want to join the Imperial Legion.

Cell.Text: [S] S|Is that right? Hmm... Well, you've come to the right place.

Node.Caption: MQ102ARikkeIntroTopic: I'd like to join the Imperial Legion.

Cell.Text: G|There are a few formalities we'll have to take care of before...
G|Go ahead in. Legate Rikke is the one you need to talk to.

Node.Caption: MQ102GuardJoinLegionTopic: I'm here to join the Legion.

Cell.Text: G|It's up to the General at this point.
Hmm. You did prove yourself mighty resourceful. Not many of us got out of there alive. | We can always use another soldier. We'll be drafting prisoners soon enough, I don't doubt.

Node.Caption: MQ102TulliusIntroB1: I don't hold a grudge. Why should you?

Cell.Text: Hadvar's alive? I hope that's true. He's a damn good soldier. But he hasn't reported in yet, so he can't exactly confirm your story. | Well... I'll take you at your word, for now. We can't afford to be too choosy about our recruits at the moment.

Node.Caption: MQ102TulliusIntroB2: I helped Hadvar escape. He said he'd vouch for me.

Cell.Text: [S] G|If a little harsh language changes your mind, you weren't Legion material anyway. | Come and see me if you decide you're ready to be a real soldier.

Node.Caption: MQ102TulliusIntroB3: I guess I don't want to join the Legion after all.

Cell.Text: You were at Helgen! One of the prisoners. | What in Oblivion are you doing here?
G|Talk to Legate Rikke. She'll decide if you're Legion material.
